  <brief_title>Masked Comparison of a New PEG Based Artificial Tear and Optive for Comfort, Vision &amp; Wear Time in Patients Wearing Contact Lenses</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase 4 Masked Comparison of a New PEG Based Artificial Tear and Optive for Comfort, Vision &amp; Wear Time in Patients Wearing Contact Lenses</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Bp Consulting, Inc</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Bp Consulting, Inc</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to evaluate the effect of a new PEG based artificial tear as
      compared to Optive on comfort, wear time, and vision in patients wearing contact lenses.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
